messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
I need a policeman in the name of this in my house. Right now.
I need you to calm down and give me the address, ma'am.
1807 Elmwood Court, Sugarland, hurry, please.
What's going on, ma'am?
She's trying to get away. She's trying to get away. Please send somebody.
Okay, I need you to tell me why. What's going on?
My husband pressed charges against her, and now she busted the door off and stabbed him. Please hurry up.
She came into your house and stabbed him? Who is she?
Please just send somebody.
Okay, he's holding her down at this point, but he's bleeding very badly.
Yes, and he's trying to hold her down, but she said she's not going to jail, so she's stabbing him.
Ma'am, I have them on the way. What is the female's name you're talking about?
Her name is Lydia. Okay, right now he's trying to hold her down and she's... oh, God!
What is she stabbing him with?
I don't know. It's not... it looks like a knife. It's sticking out of his head.
A knife?
Yes, I just don't stick it out of his head. It's still in there.
Okay, what's your name, ma'am?
My name is Cindy, and I'm sorry, but I am really freaked out right now.
Okay, I understand, ma'am, and I'm sorry, but they're on the way, okay? Who is she to you all?
She used to work for him. She stole a lot of equipment, so he pressed charges on her, and now all of a sudden she's in our house in the middle of the night.
Does she have a car, anything out there you know?
I don't know.
Do you have any kids or anything over there?
Yes, I have four.
You have four kids inside?
Yes.
Are your kids in another room?
Yes, they're upstairs asleep. Please hurry, let's hurry up.
Try to calm down, ma'am. They're on the way. They're coming as fast as they can.
I'm going to wind up killing her if she doesn't just be still. Okay, I'm gonna hit her with this baseball bat if she doesn't be still.
Ma'am, just keep her there one way or another. She's not getting away this time.
This is the problem. They couldn't find her. The police are supposed to be arresting her for the last month.
You said your husband filed a restraining order on her before?
He does, possibly. He had a warrant out for her arrest, but as usual, the police aren't doing their job.
Ma'am, you need to get that ambulance here quick. Okay, he's bleeding everywhere.
He's bleeding everywhere.
Where did she stab him?
In the head. I've already told you that.
Okay, I have that, but you said she was continuing to stab him.
That's all I can see right now.
Where are you all at in the house?
We're in the bedroom.
In the bedroom? Is the door open or anything?
I was standing in the doorway. I don't remember if I left it open or not.
Ma'am, can I please get off the phone now?
I have a bat, ma'am. If I have to, I will use it.
Okay, stay on the line. They should be coming soon, okay?
Okay, he's doing all he can to hold her down. If she moves, I'm going to hit her.
Okay, they should be coming any minute now.
Hurry, please, hurry!
Okay, ma'am, where is your bedroom located in the house? They come in the door, where do they go?
To the left, in the back.
Hurry, please, hurry! She's running.
They should be coming up, ma'am. Hold on for me.
Are you okay? They're here!
You have an officer there?
Yes, they're here. We need an ambulance.
Okay, they're coming. Stay safe.
Okay, bye.
